  "text": "Human neuroblastoma SH-SY5Y cells were maintained at 37°C in 5% CO 2 in DMEM/F12 medium (Sigma-Aldrich) with 10% fetal calf serum, penicillin-streptomycin-glutamine (Gibco), and Minimum Eagle's Medium Nonessential Amino Acid Solution (Gibco). Cells at a concentration of 1.5 ϫ 10 5 cells/ml were cultured to ϳ30 -50% confluence in collagencoated 6-well plates and transfected with pcDNA3-WT mouse ␣S or pcDNA3-FLAG-human ␣S plasmids using X-tremeGENE 9 (Roche), followed by culture for 16 h. The cells were treated with final 150 nM ␣S proteins using MultiFectam (Promega), as previously described [CITATION_1] .",
